Sam Raimi, I feel, is a filmmaker with a strong creative voice. He has a distinctive visual style and humor that would be recognizable to anyone who'd scene Evil Dead, Drag Me To Hell or even his Spider-Man films. He was certainly an interesting choice for Doctor Strange

I feel like the MCU has a tendency to dilute the creative voices of their directors. This is obviously a problem that will arise with any sufficiently profitable franchise, studio intervention in the interest of profits.
That's the lens I want to discuss #MultiverseOfMadness with
